article.description: Tarik Cool had 18 points and seven assists as Idaho State edged past Northern Arizona 71-67 on Saturday.
article.headline: Cool scores 18 to lift Idaho St. past N. Arizona 71-67
article.linkText: Cool scores 18 to lift Idaho St. past N. Arizona 71-67
article.story: FLAGSTAFF, Ariz. -- Tarik Cool had 18 points and seven assists as Idaho State edged past Northern Arizona 71-67 on Saturday. Austin Smellie had 13 points for Idaho State (6-8, 3-2 Big Sky Conference), which snapped its five-game road losing streak. Jared Stutzman added 10 points. Chidi Udengwu had eight rebounds for the visitors. Brooks DeBisschop scored a career-high 20 points and had 10 rebounds for the Lumberjacks (7-7, 1-4). Cameron Satterwhite added 13 points. Ted McCree had 12 points. Idaho State faces Weber State at home on Thursday. Northern Arizona takes on Southern Utah on the road on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
